00:29:07.300 --> 00:29:13.010
So all markets-- not
just crypto markets--

00:29:13.010 --> 00:29:17.810
all markets are susceptible to
some forms of front running.

00:29:17.810 --> 00:29:21.380
In essence, if you have
a client relationship

00:29:21.380 --> 00:29:24.470
and you get information
from your client that

00:29:24.470 --> 00:29:28.100
might affect the
market pricing, you

00:29:28.100 --> 00:29:32.480
might jump ahead of that
client with their information.

00:29:32.480 --> 00:29:36.200
Their information might be
a buy order, a sell order.

00:29:36.200 --> 00:29:38.850
Or frankly, it might be
some other information.

00:29:38.850 --> 00:29:42.170
But traditionally, if they have
a buy order or a sell order,

00:29:42.170 --> 00:29:43.790
you have information.

00:29:43.790 --> 00:29:49.300
And then you're sort of jumping
ahead and saying, all right.

00:29:49.300 --> 00:29:51.190
I'll buy or sell
in front of them.

00:29:51.190 --> 00:29:53.710
That's the classic
sort of front running,

00:29:53.710 --> 00:29:57.550
even though there's
other methods.

00:29:57.550 --> 00:29:59.050
It's not supposed to happen.

00:29:59.050 --> 00:30:04.870
On regulated exchanges, you
have some policing of it.

00:30:04.870 --> 00:30:06.640
Even before
governments stood in,

00:30:06.640 --> 00:30:08.110
you could have
some policing of it

00:30:08.110 --> 00:30:11.590
in self-regulatory
organizations.

00:30:11.590 --> 00:30:16.600
In the crypto world, there
is Katy bar the door.

00:30:16.600 --> 00:30:18.670
Anything can really happen.

00:30:18.670 --> 00:30:21.820
And it's my belief
and understanding

00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:24.940
that many crypto
exchanges-- not all of them.

00:30:24.940 --> 00:30:25.670
Not all of them.

00:30:25.670 --> 00:30:27.940
But many crypto
exchanges are basically

00:30:27.940 --> 00:30:32.200
trading in front
of their customers.

00:30:32.200 --> 00:30:35.590
And in fact, most
crypto exchanges

00:30:35.590 --> 00:30:39.190
make markets, as they
are both market makers--

00:30:39.190 --> 00:30:42.430
meaning they are buying when
you're selling and selling

00:30:42.430 --> 00:30:43.390
when you're buying.

00:30:43.390 --> 00:30:45.300
That's the nature
of a market maker.

00:30:45.300 --> 00:30:48.490
It's very typical, very
legal, very important

00:30:48.490 --> 00:30:49.750
function of market.

00:30:49.750 --> 00:30:52.720
But the exchanges are
both market makers,

00:30:52.720 --> 00:30:54.790
and then they show order books.

00:30:54.790 --> 00:31:00.120
And so it sort of helps
them do front running.

00:31:00.120 --> 00:31:03.030
Not that a lot of people
