are not blockchain--

00:32:13.382 --> 00:32:15.090
they're not permissioned,
and they're not

00:32:15.090 --> 00:32:16.390
permissionless blockchain.

00:32:16.390 --> 00:32:19.740
But if you look at both the
algorithms and the data flows,

00:32:19.740 --> 00:32:22.023
they have very
good timestamping.

00:32:22.023 --> 00:32:23.440
I'm not going to
say it's perfect,

00:32:23.440 --> 00:32:24.940
but they have very
good timestamping

00:32:24.940 --> 00:32:28.440
to ensure when are orders--

00:32:28.440 --> 00:32:32.630
basically message timestamping
every message that comes in.

00:32:32.630 --> 00:32:36.300
And some order books, like
the New York Stock Exchange--

00:32:36.300 --> 00:32:41.280
some order books are
price and time priority,

00:32:41.280 --> 00:32:45.960
price priority meaning high bid
gets hit before the next bid,

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:49.800
or lowest offer
gets lifted first.

00:32:49.800 --> 00:32:51.720
That's price priority.

00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:53.670
But they might also
have time priority

00:32:53.670 --> 00:32:57.570
for any bid that has the same
price and any offer that's

00:32:57.570 --> 00:32:59.040
the same price.

00:32:59.040 --> 00:33:01.140
So they have to have
very good timestamping.

00:33:05.730 --> 00:33:08.040
I truly believe you could
not use a blockchain

00:33:08.040 --> 00:33:12.540
